<subSubSection id="A6D23D89FFDD0F2CFF00FB07FB669B73" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="151" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EE776E02FFDD0F2FFF00FB07FD679C46" blockId="5.[151,1437,1265,2012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDD0F2FFF00FB07FDDB9F1A" bold="true" box="[151,586,1265,1292]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Distribution and additional records.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="29C81581FFDD0F2FFDC4FB04FC9D9F1A" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[595,780,1266,1292]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalinus">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDD0F2FFDC4FB04FC9D9F1A" box="[595,780,1266,1292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Brycon opalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known from the upper rio 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFB61FB04FADB9F1A" box="[1270,1354,1266,1292]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Paraíba</collectingRegion>
do Sul and upper rio Doce basins in the states of 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFD17FAE0FD679F26" box="[640,758,1302,1328]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFC94FAE0FC3D9F26" box="[771,940,1302,1328]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFC7CFAE0FB179F26" box="[1003,1158,1302,1328]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="96DF2E92FFDD0F2FFB04FAE0FB469F26" box="[1171,1239,1302,1328]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDD0F2FFB7FFAE0FAFD9F26" author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[1256,1388,1302,1328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Lima 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Its current geographical range is highly fragmented and restricted to some headwater tributaries of the rio 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFAB3FACCFAE99F42" box="[1316,1400,1338,1364]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Paraíba</collectingRegion>
do Sul and rio Doce basins, with relatively healthy populations in some river stretches (
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDD0F2FFBCCFAA8FB4C9F6E" author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[1115,1245,1374,1400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Lima 2017</bibRefCitation>
). There is an old record for the species downstream from the rio Doce in 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFC84FA74FC669F8A" box="[787,1015,1410,1436]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Espírito Santo State</collectingRegion>
, considered doubtful by 
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDD0F2FFA99FA74FA0D9F8A" author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[1294,1436,1410,1436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Lima (2017)</bibRefCitation>
in view of the known preference of the species for headwater areas. 
<taxonomicName id="29C81581FFDD0F2FFC07FA50FBD99FD6" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[912,1096,1446,1472]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalinus">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDD0F2FFC07FA50FBD99FD6" box="[912,1096,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Brycon opalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded herein for the first time from the rio Itapemirim (
<figureCitation id="76F37287FFDD0F2FFE77FA3CFDAB9FF2" box="[480,570,1481,1508]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,973,997]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,381,949]" captionTargetId="figure-139@6.[151,1436,381,949]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Brycon opalinus, MBML 9587, 145.9 mm SL: Brazil, Espírito Santo, rio Itapemirim basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5733636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5733636/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">figure 5</figureCitation>
), a river system located in the southern portion of the 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFB1EFA3CFAF89FF2" box="[1161,1385,1482,1508]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Espírito Santo State</collectingRegion>
. The specimens were all sampled in the upper rio Itapemirim basin, in the rio Braço Norte Direito, on a stretch limited upstream by Parque Estadual da Cachoeira da Fumaça (PECF) and downstream by Central Geradora Hidrelétrica (CGH) Francisco Gross, near the mouth of tributaries.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE776E02FFDD0F2FFF50F9AFFDD29DAE" blockId="5.[151,1437,1265,2012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDD0F2FFF50F9AFFD9E9C62" bold="true" box="[199,527,1625,1652]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Habitat and ecological notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="29C81581FFDD0F2FFD8DF9ACFD5E9C62" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[538,719,1626,1652]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalinus">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDD0F2FFD8DF9ACFD5E9C62" box="[538,719,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Brycon opalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in headwater areas, inhabiting small rivers, characterized by possessing slightly dark-stained to clear waters, and lentic stretches alternated with rapids (
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDD0F2FFB53F988FAD79C8E" author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[1220,1350,1662,1688]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFB53F988FA909C8E" box="[1220,1281,1662,1688]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Lima</collectingRegion>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingCounty id="0716168EFFDD0F2FFACFF988FAED9C8E" box="[1368,1404,1662,1688]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">All</collectingCounty>
<taxonomicName id="29C81581FFDD0F2FFA13F988FF669CAA" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1819" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalinus">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDD0F2FFA13F988FF669CAA" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">B. opalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens collected in the 
<collectingMunicipality id="0E13F478FFDD0F2FFDADF954FD4E9CAA" box="[570,735,1698,1724]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">rio Itapemirim</collectingMunicipality>
basin were found in stretches close to rapids. 
<location id="EB1738D9FFDD0F2FFB6CF954FAB69CAA" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:6661DF14FFDD0F2CFF00FB70FB669B73:EB1738D9FFDD0F2FFB6CF954FAB69CAA" box="[1275,1319,1698,1724]" county="All" municipality="rio Itapemirim" name="The" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" stateProvince="Lima">The</location>
<location id="EB1738D9FFDD0F2FFAA6F954FEBF9CF6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:6661DF14FFDD0F2CFF00FB70FB669B73:EB1738D9FFDD0F2FFAA6F954FEBF9CF6" county="All" municipality="rio Itapemirim" name="rio Braco Norte Direito" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" stateProvince="Lima">rio Braço Norte Direito</location>
near 
<location id="EB1738D9FFDD0F2FFEF9F930FCD69CF6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:6661DF14FFDD0F2CFF00FB70FB669B73:EB1738D9FFDD0F2FFEF9F930FCD69CF6" box="[366,839,1734,1760]" county="All" municipality="rio Itapemirim" name="Parque Estadual da Cachoeira da Fumaca" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" stateProvince="Lima">Parque Estadual da Cachoeira da Fumaça</location>
, where the species was first recorded in this basin in the years 2012 and 2013, had a maximum width of 
<quantity id="2930C3E7FFDD0F2FFD4AF91FFCBF9D12" box="[733,814,1769,1796]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.86" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" unit="m" value="28.6">
<elevation id="65E58931FFDD0F2FFD4AF91FFCBF9D12" box="[733,814,1769,1796]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.86" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" unit="m" value="28.6">28.6 m</elevation>
</quantity>
, a maximum depth of about 
<quantity id="2930C3E7FFDD0F2FFBE6F91CFB259D12" box="[1137,1204,1770,1796]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" unit="m" value="2.2">
<elevation id="65E58931FFDD0F2FFBE6F91CFB259D12" box="[1137,1204,1770,1796]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" unit="m" value="2.2">2.2 m</elevation>
</quantity>
, and the river in this stretch has a fast current with rapids. The substrate is composed mainly of sand and pebbles, with scattered rocks. Water transparency in this river varies markedly throughout the year, with relatively low turbidity and clear waters during the dry season, and turbid waters, with low transparency, during the rainy season. The catchment area of the 
<location id="EB1738D9FFDD0F2FFF00F88CFE329D82" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:6661DF14FFDD0F2CFF00FB70FB669B73:EB1738D9FFDD0F2FFF00F88CFE329D82" box="[151,419,1914,1940]" county="All" municipality="rio Itapemirim" name="rio Braco Norte Direito" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" stateProvince="Lima">rio Braço Norte Direito</location>
is mostly deforested, being mainly composed of pastureland, with a few more vegetated areas in an initial phase of succession.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE776E02FFDD0F2CFF50F834FB669B73" blockId="5.[151,1437,1265,2012]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="151" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName id="29C81581FFDD0F2FFF50F834FE119DCA" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[199,384,1986,2012]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalinus">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDD0F2FFF50F834FE119DCA" box="[199,384,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Brycon opalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not known to undertake large migrations (
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDD0F2FFCEDF834FC6A9DCA" author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[890,1019,1986,2012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDD0F2FFCEDF834FC269DCA" box="[890,951,1986,2012]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Lima</collectingRegion>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). It is likely that this species uses the rio Braço Norte Direito as a migratory corridor and spawning area (this river stretch is approximately 
<quantity id="2930C3E7FFDE0F2CFA9BFF61FAC29AA7" box="[1292,1363,151,177]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" unit="km" value="18.0">18 km</quantity>
long). This assumption is based on the fact that only juveniles were recorded within the Parque Estadual da Cachoeira da Fumaça (PECF) (
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDE0F2CFE1EFF29FDD49AEF" author="Rodrigues, L. N." box="[393,581,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" refId="ref11660" refString="Rodrigues, L. N. (2013) Ictiofauna do Parque Estadual da Cachoeira da Fumaca, Alegre-Ibitirama, regiao sul do ES Ictiofauna do Parque Estadual da Cachoeira da Fumaca, Alegre-Ibitirama, regiao sul do ES. Universidade Federal do Espirito Santo, Alegre, 50 pp." type="book" year="2013">
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDE0F2CFE1EFF29FE6F9AEF" box="[393,510,223,249]" country="Mauritius" name="Rodrigues" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Rodrigues</collectingRegion>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
), which is situated downstream from a waterfall 144 meters high, which corresponds to a natural barrier for most of the aquatic fauna in this river. The PECF protects a preserved section of rio Braço Norte Direito, one of the main tributaries forming the rio Itapemirim. While the few recorded adult specimens were found downstream from the PECF, in the area comprised by CGH Francisco Gross.
</paragraph>
